If you were working a corporate job in the mid-to-late-2000&rsquo;s, you&rsquo;ve probably experienced &ldquo;offshoring.&rdquo;
The leadership team brings in a bunch of new remote employees in a country with much cheaper labor costs and less stringent labor laws that yours. They ask you to help train them and teach them everything you know so they can &ldquo;get up to speed quickly.&rdquo;
And then six months later, they lay off your whole team and keep the offshore workers.
